This product includes software developed by third parties.

Friday Studio ships several artifacts, each of which bundles a different set of
upstream dependencies:

  - Atlas daemon, CLI, and web playground (Deno + npm + JSR packages)
  - Friday Launcher, pty-server, webhook-tunnel (Go modules)
  - Studio Installer (Rust crates via Cargo / Tauri)

The complete inventory of every third-party dependency, its version, license,
and source URL is generated from the project's lockfiles and recorded in
THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.md at the root of this repository.

Run `bash scripts/generate-third-party-licenses.sh` to regenerate the inventory
after a dependency bump.

Release artifacts (the macOS / Windows installers and the compiled Go binaries)
include a copy of THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.md alongside the executable, satisfying
the attribution requirements of MIT, BSD, Apache-2.0, MPL-2.0, and ISC license
families. The full text of any individual license can be retrieved from the
locations described in the "How to retrieve full license text" section of
THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.md.

